          "Road -> Ocean -> Road"
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC12",
      "type": "heading",
      "title": "Business Scenario"
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC13",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "A company transports products from Hyderabad Plant to Chennai Distribution Center. SAP TM validates the Transportation Lane, checks the assigned carrier and available resources, then creates an optimized Freight Order using the configured route."
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC14",
      "type": "comparison",
      "title": "Transportation Lane vs Transportation Zone",
      "leftTitle": "Transportation Lane",
      "rightTitle": "Transportation Zone",
      "rows": [
        {
          "feature": "Purpose",
          "left": "Defines Route",
          "right": "Groups Locations"
        },
        {
          "feature": "Planning",
          "left": "Route Selection",
          "right": "Regional Planning"
        },
        {
          "feature": "Relationship",
          "left": "Between Two Locations",
          "right": "Collection of Locations"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC15",
      "type": "heading",
      "title": "Business Benefits"
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC16",
      "type": "bullet-list",
      "items": [
        "Accurate route determination",
        "Improved carrier selection",
        "Better transportation optimization",
        "Reduced planning errors",
        "Reliable transit time calculation",
        "Efficient shipment execution"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC17",
      "type": "callout",
      "calloutType": "best-practice",
      "title": "Best Practice",
      "content": "Maintain Transportation Lanes at the Transportation Zone level whenever possible to reduce master data maintenance and simplify planning."
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC18",
      "type": "callout",
      "calloutType": "example",
      "title": "Real Project Example",
      "content": "An international logistics company reduced over 25,000 individual Transportation Lanes to 2,300 zone-based lanes, significantly reducing maintenance effort while improving optimizer performance."
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC19",
      "type": "callout",
      "calloutType": "interview-tip",
      "title": "Interview Tip",
      "content": "A Transportation Lane defines whether transportation between two locations is possible and specifies the route, carrier and transportation mode used for planning."
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC20",
      "type": "callout",
      "calloutType": "warning",
      "title": "Common Mistake",
      "content": "Transportation Lanes do not represent actual shipments. They are master data used during transportation planning."
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC21",
      "type": "heading",
      "title": "Revision Summary"
    },
    {
      "id": "SEC22",
      "type": "bullet-list",
      "items": [
        "Transportation Lanes connect source and destination locations.",
        "They define valid transportation routes.",
        "Transportation Lanes support planning and optimization.",
        "Transportation Lanes can use Road, Rail, Air or Ocean modes.",
        "Transportation Lanes are master data, not transactional documents."
      ]
    }
